{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3449f1de-bcba-4930-89ab-b6863c265ab7","content":"The official MCP Registry is maintained at **github.com/modelcontextprotocol/servers**. To get your server listed:\n\n1. **Fork** the [modelcontextprotocol/servers](https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/servers) repository.\n2. **Add an entry** for your server — typically by editing the registry's index/README or adding a JSON entry (check the repo's `CONTRIBUTING.md` for the exact format).\n3. **Open a Pull Request** with details about your server: name, description, NuGet package link, and what tools/resources it exposes.\n\nThe maintainers will review and merge it once it meets their guidelines.\n\nWant me to fetch the repo's contributing guide for the exact submission format?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3b444c19-e942-485e-84b9-a61ef6356eee","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to register their C# MCP server in the official MCP Registry. This is a general knowledge question about the MCP (Model Context Protocol) ecosystem. Let me provide what I know about this process.\n\nLet me check if there's any relevant information I can find about the MCP Registry.","outputTokens":257,"requestId":"AC14:1B520F:B4D501:E0C604:6A012DA4"},"id":"b21951b0-8e63-4913-a66c-175eef159d3c","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:15:25.521Z","parentId":"3daf3edc-fdc8-4243-b6fb-ce4342b477ea"}
